# rexglue Vulkan SDK patch for NHL Legacy
#
# Apply against a clean checkout of the rexglue SDK (E:\Tools\rexglue-sdk\src):
#   git apply docs/rexglue-vulkan-nhl-legacy.patch
#
# Captures the Vulkan-fsi rendering source changes: spirv translator + texture
# cache fixes (exp_adjust word3, readback=full, signed BC5) AND the in-game
# color-grade post-process (command_processor.{cpp,h}: present_grade_* cvars +
# the grade compute pipeline/dispatch after the swap gamma-apply).
#
# The grade compute shader is NOT in this diff (the SDK shaders dir is generated
# and not reliably tracked). Copy the two canonical files from this repo into the
# SDK tree before building:
#   renderer/shaders/nhl_grade.comp   -> src/graphics/vulkan/shaders/src/nhl_grade.comp
#   renderer/shaders/nhl_grade_cs.h   -> src/graphics/vulkan/shaders/nhl_grade_cs.h
# (regenerate the header after editing the shader:
#   glslangValidator -V --vn nhl_grade_cs nhl_grade.comp -o ../nhl_grade_cs.h)
#
# The FidelityFX cmake/build changes are documented separately in
# docs/fidelityfx-enablement-notes.md.
#
